Build an Electron app called "Switchboard" — a Slack-style multi-session 
terminal manager for Claude Code workflows.

STACK: Electron, React, xterm.js, node-pty

LAYOUT:
- Left sidebar (~220px): list of project session tabs, each showing project 
  name and status indicator dot
- Main area: active terminal (xterm.js), full height/width minus sidebar
- Header bar: active project name, "+ New Session" button, settings icon

SESSION TABS (sidebar):
- Each tab has: colored dot (left), project name, optional short path label
- Dot states: 
    green = Claude is working (output is flowing)
    yellow = idle/quiet (no output for 10s, prompt not yet detected)
    red pulsing = waiting for input (Claude Code prompt detected)
- Clicking a tab switches the active terminal pane; background tabs keep 
  running via node-pty, their xterm.js instances remain mounted but hidden 
  (display:none, not destroyed)

IDLE DETECTION:
- In the main process, watch each pty's output stream
- Claude Code's ready-for-input state shows a prompt matching: 
  /^[>❯]\s*$/m or similar — treat this as configurable via a 
  PROMPT_PATTERN env var or settings JSON
- When pattern detected after ≥2 seconds of activity: emit 
  session-needs-attention IPC event for that session ID
- When user sends any input to a session: emit session-working IPC event
- Also trigger yellow state after 10s of no output if red hasn't triggered yet

SESSION MANAGEMENT:
- "+ New Session" opens a modal: project name (text), working directory 
  (path picker), optional shell command override (default: "claude")
- Sessions persist in a local JSON file (sessions.json) so app remembers 
  them on relaunch
- Right-click a tab: rename, change directory, close session

NOTIFICATIONS:
- When any background tab flips to red (needs-attention) and the app is 
  not focused: show a native OS desktop notification with the project name
- Optional: system tray icon badge showing count of sessions needing attention

TERMINAL:
- xterm.js with FitAddon (fills available space), WebLinksAddon
- Theme: dark, match system accent color or configurable
- Each session gets its own xterm.js Terminal instance, persisted for the 
  app lifetime (switching tabs does display:none swap, not remount)

NON-GOALS for this version:
- No session sharing/collaboration
- No SSH remoting
- No split panes

Start with: main.js (Electron main), preload.js, App.jsx (root React), 
Sidebar.jsx, TerminalPane.jsx, sessionManager.js (node-pty + IPC logic), 
and a basic package.json with all deps.
